sequenceDiagram
    participant MM as ModelMesh Container
    participant Puller as model-serving-puller<br/>8084/TCP gRPC
    participant Storage as Cloud Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Adapter as Runtime Adapter<br/>8085/TCP gRPC
    participant Runtime as Model Runtime<br/>(Triton/MLServer/OVMS/TorchServe)
    participant FS as Local Filesystem<br/>/models

    Note over MM,Runtime: Flow 1: Model Loading

    MM->>Puller: loadModel(modelId, modelPath)<br/>gRPC :8084 plaintext
    Puller->>Storage: Download model artifacts<br/>HTTPS :443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Access Key / OAuth2 / Azure AD
    Storage-->>Puller: Model files
    Puller->>FS: Write model to /models/{modelId}
    Puller->>Adapter: loadModel(modelId, localPath)<br/>gRPC :8085 plaintext
    Adapter->>Adapter: Adapt model layout for runtime<br/>(directory structure, config files)
    Adapter->>Runtime: Native load API<br/>gRPC :8001 or :7071 plaintext
    Runtime-->>Adapter: Load confirmation
    Adapter-->>Puller: ModelResponse(size, maxConcurrency)
    Puller-->>MM: ModelResponse(size, maxConcurrency)

    Note over MM,Runtime: Flow 2: Model Unloading

    MM->>Puller: unloadModel(modelId)<br/>gRPC :8084 plaintext
    Puller->>Adapter: unloadModel(modelId)<br/>gRPC :8085 plaintext
    Adapter->>Runtime: Native unload API<br/>gRPC :8001 or :7071 plaintext
    Runtime-->>Adapter: Unload confirmation
    Adapter-->>Puller: UnloadModelResponse
    Puller->>FS: Delete /models/{modelId}
    Puller-->>MM: UnloadModelResponse

    Note over MM,Runtime: Flow 3: Runtime Status Check (Startup)

    MM->>Puller: runtimeStatus()<br/>gRPC :8084 plaintext
    Puller->>Adapter: runtimeStatus()<br/>gRPC :8085 plaintext
    Adapter->>Runtime: Health/readiness check<br/>gRPC or HTTP plaintext
    Runtime-->>Adapter: Status response
    Adapter-->>Puller: RuntimeStatusResponse<br/>(STARTING/READY/FAILING,<br/>capacity, concurrency,<br/>supported methods)
    Puller-->>MM: RuntimeStatusResponse
